<i> and an edge on the bottom,</i>

04:03.827 --> 04:05.953
<i> so that when they test it</i>
<i> on the fish,</i>

04:05.996 --> 04:08.914
it'll still make a nice cut.

04:08.958 --> 04:12.876
- What I'm gonna
make is something curvy,

04:12.920 --> 04:15.963
<i> because I thought it would</i>
<i> add a little extra style</i>

04:16.006 --> 04:19.549
<i> to set myself apart</i>
<i> from my competitors.</i>

04:19.593 --> 04:22.678
<i> I'm trying to make</i>
<i> something that's futuristic.</i>

04:22.721 --> 04:25.681
- Bladesmiths, your design
period has closed.

04:25.724 --> 04:28.976
Your three-hour
forging time starts now.

04:29.019 --> 04:31.478
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:31.522 --> 04:33.605
- All right.

04:33.649 --> 04:35.107
<i> - Looking at the steel,</i>
<i> that's just way too much</i>

04:35.150 --> 04:36.984
steel to make a blade.

04:37.027 --> 04:39.236
I can probably make two or
three blades out of that thing.

04:39.280 --> 04:41.697
- So, Matt is chopping it up
on the chop saw.

04:41.740 --> 04:44.074
He's got pieces in the forge.

